{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Locate to marker ID via OSC\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Written by Ben Smith - July 2021\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Info\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The default option for moving the Reaper's playhead to a particular marker only works with the order of markers.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab This script allows you to specify a marker number (i.e. marker ID) to navigate to.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Usage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Trigger this script via OSC (either a custom command, or /action).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab As an argument in your OSC command, include the marker ID you wish to locate to divided by 1000.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab E.g. for marker 21, send {\f1 /action/XXXXXX 0.021}.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab This is because the reaper.get_action_context() command will only return the value of an OSC message if it is between 0 and 1.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The resolution of the interpreted value is 16383.\sa180\par}
}

