{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Arm tracks for recording\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Written by Ben Smith - 2021\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Info\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Arm a specific set of tracks for recording \u8211-\u160?customise a version of this script for use with your project.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Useful when you are regularly arming and disarming the same group of tracks, but do not want to arm every track in the project (e.g. recording a multitrack performance, and you have groups or folders).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab "Arm all tracks within folders" is more useful, if that is what you need this for.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 User customisation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab tracksToArm\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab A list of all tracks you wish to toggle.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab rangeToArm\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab A range of tracks which should all be toggled.\sa180\sa180\par}
}

